Meditation
//MainActivity Start your journey Finding your inner peace is something that should be done 5-10 minutes every day. It will help you grow and relieve you from stress. Now open your mind, clear your head and lets go! Press to let your journey begin FIND YOUR INNER PEACE CLEAR YOUR HEAD
//FirstActivity Meditate Focus on breathing in an out. Breath in from the mouth and out of your nose. Try t relax and keep your mind clear. Do this for 3-5 minutes.
//SecondActivity Silence Turn off every electronic device and surrond yourself with the silence and listen to your inner self.
//ThirdActivity Go walking Take you headphones and head out to the nature for a relaxing walk.
//FourthActivity Yoga Now I want you to do five yoga exercises. Take the time you need and do not forget to breath slowly.
//FifthActivity Tea time We all now that a cup of tea is both good for your body and mental state. Now I want you to go make a cup of tea with and enjoy a relaxing time with either a book or in front of the tv.
//SixthActivity Taking notes Focus on what makes you happy and write down three of those things. Place the note in your pocket and be sure to always bring it with you.
//SeventhActivity Thank somebody Who makes you happy? Who brings you the most joy? Why not say thank you to that person?
//EightActivity Read a book Pick up your favorite book and lose yourself in its fantasy world!
//NineActivity Write Writing is one way to handle stress and is both stimulating for your brain and may help you relieve stress and anxiety!
//TenthActivity Play Play is a wonderful way to unwind! Play is anything that is purposeless and pleasurable. Go out to throw a Frisbee or go to the zoo, anything that is fun for you.
//EleventhActivity Be in nature Head outside and “sit on a bench or a blanket and let your mind get quiet” while you engage all your senses. Engaging your senses is a powerful way to relax. What do you see, hear and smell?
//TwelfthActivity Set goals Setting yourself goals and challenges, whether at work or outside, such as learning a new language or training, can help you switch off from the high pressures in life and build your confidence.
//ThirteenActivity Exercise Exercise is one of the most important things you can do to combat stress.People who exercise regularly are less likely to experience anxiety than those who dont exercise.
//FourteenActivity Have company Solitude and silence can be the ultimate way to relax. For others, there is nothing more diverting than enjoying the company of your loved ones. Whether they provide a distraction or they help you.
